1. any pytestdemo file should start with test_ or end with _test
2. pytestdemo method should start with test
3. any test should be wrapped in function only

Running test cases in terminal/cmd prompt
1. copy path of directory ex: cd /Users/sagarkamthane/PycharmProjects/pytestdemo
2. go to that directory in terminal
3. hit py.test
4. py.test -v (v: verbrose, shows more information)
5. py.test -v -s (also prints the output)
6. to run a specific file use : py.test pytestpractice/test_demo1.py -v -s
7. to run a specific tesecase from any file use: py.test -k case1 -v -s
   -k : test case execution by method name
   -v : more info in metadata
   -s : logs and output in metadata
8. to run a test case with with specific tag ex: @pytest.mark.smoke use py.test -m smoke  -v -s


Fixtures:
1. use @pytest.fixture to define a module as a fixture
2. that module will be treated as a precondition
3.

to generate report use --html = report.html
py.test -s -v --html=report.html
